## Docker Configuration

### Building Images

- Build image: `docker build -t <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest .`
- Build with tag: `docker build -t <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:<version> .`
- Build with no cache: `docker build --no-cache -t <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest .`
- Build with build args: `docker build --build-arg KEY=value -t <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest .`
- Build for specific platform: `docker build --platform linux/amd64 -t <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest .`

### Running Containers

- Run container: `docker run <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest`
- Run with port mapping: `docker run -p <PLACEHOLDER: PORTS>:<PLACEHOLDER: PORTS> <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest`
- Run in background: `docker run -d <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest`
- Run with name: `docker run --name <container-name> <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest`
- Run with environment file: `docker run --env-file .env <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest`
- Run with environment variables: `docker run -e KEY=value <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest`
- Run with volume: `docker run -v /host/path:/container/path <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest`
- Run with network: `docker run --network <network-name> <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest`
- Run interactively: `docker run -it <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest /bin/bash`

### Container Management

- List running containers: `docker ps`
- List all containers: `docker ps -a`
- Stop container: `docker stop <container-id>`
- Start container: `docker start <container-id>`
- Restart container: `docker restart <container-id>`
- Remove container: `docker rm <container-id>`
- Remove running container: `docker rm -f <container-id>`
- View container logs: `docker logs <container-id>`
- Follow logs: `docker logs -f <container-id>`
- Execute command in container: `docker exec -it <container-id> <command>`
- Inspect container: `docker inspect <container-id>`

### Image Management

- List images: `docker images`
- Remove image: `docker rmi <image-id>`
- Remove all unused images: `docker image prune -a`
- Tag image: `docker tag <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:<version>`
- Push to registry: `docker push <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:<version>`
- Pull from registry: `docker pull <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:<version>`
- Inspect image: `docker inspect <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest`
- View image history: `docker history <PLACEHOLDER: PROJECT_NAME>:latest`

### Docker Compose

- Start services: `docker-compose up`
- Start in background: `docker-compose up -d`
- Stop services: `docker-compose down`
- Stop and remove volumes: `docker-compose down -v`
- Rebuild and start: `docker-compose up --build`
- Rebuild specific service: `docker-compose build <service-name>`
- Start specific service: `docker-compose up <service-name>`
- View logs: `docker-compose logs`
- Follow logs: `docker-compose logs -f`
- View logs for service: `docker-compose logs -f <service-name>`
- Scale services: `docker-compose up --scale <service-name>=3`
- Execute command in service: `docker-compose exec <service-name> <command>`
- Restart service: `docker-compose restart <service-name>`
- Stop service: `docker-compose stop <service-name>`
- Remove stopped containers: `docker-compose rm`

### Docker Networks

- List networks: `docker network ls`
- Create network: `docker network create <network-name>`
- Inspect network: `docker network inspect <network-name>`
- Remove network: `docker network rm <network-name>`
- Connect container to network: `docker network connect <network-name> <container-id>`
- Disconnect container from network: `docker network disconnect <network-name> <container-id>`

### Docker Volumes

- List volumes: `docker volume ls`
- Create volume: `docker volume create <volume-name>`
- Inspect volume: `docker volume inspect <volume-name>`
- Remove volume: `docker volume rm <volume-name>`
- Remove unused volumes: `docker volume prune`

### Docker System

- System information: `docker system info`
- Disk usage: `docker system df`
- Clean up: `docker system prune`
- Clean up all: `docker system prune -a`
- Remove unused resources: `docker system prune -a --volumes`

### Docker Health Checks

- Health check status: `docker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' <container-id>`
- Health check logs: `docker inspect --format='{{json .State.Health.Log}}' <container-id>`

## Best Practices

- Use multi-stage builds for smaller images
- Use .dockerignore to exclude unnecessary files
- Use specific tags instead of `latest` in production
- Run containers as non-root user when possible
- Use health checks for long-running containers
- Clean up unused images and containers regularly
- Use Docker Compose for multi-container applications
- Use named volumes for persistent data


